SASS Installation Steps
This script outlines the steps taken to install Sass:

Install Node Version Manager (NVM):
Open your terminal and run the following command to download and install NVM:
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

Reopen Terminal:
Close and then reopen your terminal to ensure NVM is properly initialized.

Install Sass:
With Node.js installed, use the Node Package Manager (npm) to install Sass:
npm install sass@3.7.4